    <string name="activity_instructions_placement">Home screen placement</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_different_ways">There are different ways to place a widget onto your home screen, the most common being:</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_1">1. On a home screen, touch and hold an empty space.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_2">2. Tap </string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_3">3. Scroll though the widgets until you find the <b>Quote Unquote</b> widget.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_4">4. Touch and slide the widget to where you want it. Lift your finger.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_5">5. <b>IMPORTANT:</b> use Android\'s \"Back\" button / gesture to successfully leave the configuration screen and place the widget on your home screen.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_configure">Once the widget is on the home screen, tap the quotation text to re-configure the widget.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_resize">Resize the widget</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_resize_instruction_1">1. Touch and hold the widget on your home screen.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_resize_instruction_2">2. Lift your finger. You\'ll find an outline with dots on the sides.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_resize_instruction_3">3. To resize the widget, drag the dots.</string>
    <string name="activity_instructions_resize_instruction_4">4. When you\'re done, tap outside the widget.</string>
